The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 December is 14,339 (1,659.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 December, there were 2,301 new confirmed cases (266.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 December, there were 1,161 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 98% (1,140 extra cases).
